"""
Filesystem Driver Interface — shared trait surface for FAT32, NVFS-native, and NVFS-POSIX.

@tag:stdlib
@tag:api

This module defines the contract that all filesystem drivers must satisfy.
Concrete implementations live in driver-specific submodules or examples/ submodules.
No dyn; all dispatch is via exhaustive match on DriverInstance.

Submodules:
  - capability:   Capability enum (22 variants) + CapabilitySet bitmask struct.
  - error:        FsError enum + errno_of() POSIX mapping.
  - types:        Shared primitives: Inode, FileHandle, DirHandle, FileMode,
                  Offset, Path, FsStatfs, FileStat, DirEntry, MountOptions, OpenFlags.
  - ops:          FsDriver trait (signatures only; no bodies).
  - extension:    Extension enum + per-cap handle stubs (*Ext structs).
  - instance:     DriverInstance enum + stub driver structs (Fat32FsStub, etc.).
  - mount_table:  MountTable, MountEntry, MountId, resolve/lookup helpers.

Adopted design: Option E' (enum-wrapped extension handle) + G-inspired DriverInstance.
See: doc/05_design/fs_driver_interface.md §1 for rationale.

Agents B/C/D fill in: Fat32FsStub, NvfsDriverStub, NvfsPosixDriverStub, and all *Ext structs.
"""

# All submodules are automatically available.
